JOHANNESBURG - KIA Motors South Africa is recalling over a thousand Rio cars.The company said this is to fix a fault on the operation of the rear door child lock system.The recall will only affect the 2017 models, which the automaker said were assembled in Korea between April and June.READ: Mazda SA recalls 19,000 carsKia is not the only car maker forced to recently make a recall locally.Ford Motors previously recalled its Kuga models, after dozens of them caught fire. eNCA